The paper presents a data-driven deep learning model for correcting numerical precipitation prediction, which involves the use of autoencoder and ordinal regression blocks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of meteorological data and visualization, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning models also suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the correction of biased predictions, which suggests that it may also belong to the Statistics (cs.SD) sub-category.
